  "title": "How can I use the getQueryStringFromState function?",
  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nI want to use the https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/reference.html#algoliasearchHelper.module:url.getQueryStringFromState function but I keep getting the message that this function doesn't exist. \r\n\r\nI'm using it in the render function of a widget and when I console.log the args passed in the render function I can't find the url module in the helper data.\r\n\r\nWhat am I doing wrong?\r\n\r\nI'm trying to build a extension that handles the <link rel=\"next\" and rel=\"prev\" in the <head> but to do that I need to get the query string - so I can get the right url for the next pages with their filters. Im using instantsearch.js 1.10.3\r\n\r\nTried to add this to discourse.algolia.com but I keep getting 403 error.",
